hopobject.body: perfect design thanks iqpc pharma iq My sense is that we will see a movement against this kind of price discrimination at least in some product/sectors. Eg fin services firms are now prohibited from using gender to price products like car insurance in the EU. OK, this is linked to equality legislations, but I suspect if companies start charging different prices based on things like postcodes then some sort of troubles await. This is the sort of issue that can kick off a boycottretty quickly once many people become aware of it – think Starbucks tax avoidance in the UK kind of boycott.
